Hobbies vs Passions

Hobbies are activities done for enjoyment or to fill the time;
Passions are skills to learn, develop and grow.

Hobbies are attended to when we have time;
Passions are what we make time for.

Hobbies are mood & situation-dependent;
Passions are pursued in spite of moods and situations.

Hobbies are dream-driven;
Passions are goal-driven.

Hobbies may not be obsessions;
Passions can be obsessions.

Hobbies can be self-indulging;
Passions can be transformative.

Hobbies may cost money;
Passions may make us loads of money.

Others may decide our hobbies for us;
Only we can decide what our passions are.

Hobbies may lead us to our passions;
Passions may lead us to our purpose.

We have hobbies;
Passions have us.

What is your hobby?
What is your passion?

#ShreyaWrites

P.S. Without business skills, your passion or hobby will not translate into money in your pocket.

~ Ehab Atalla

